      • checkSettings

        @Nullable
default String checkSettings()

        Allow to forbid user to create project will invalid settings. To do this, add validation code to this method and return text with error.
        If no errors are found return null

        This method will be called on template choose in project creation wizard and after new project path is transferred via setProjectPath(java.lang.String).

        Force project creation wizard to check and update error message state after settings changes,
        by calling fireSettingsChanged().

        Returns:
        Error text to display in project creation wizard or null if settings are valid.
